content:
OmniScripts Range Element

Enables users to select a number from a specified range by adding the Range element to your OmniScript. Specify the increment values and use both dynamic and static values to define the minimum and maximum values for the range.

Drag a Range element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
In Step, enter an increment value of the input range. For example, enter 2 so the user can select 2, 4, 6, 8, and 10 from a range of 2 to 10, or 4.5, 6.5, 8.5, and 10.5 from a range of 4.5 to 10.5.

To create a selectable range configure the following properties:

Minimum Value: Sets the lowest selectable number in the range.
Maximum Value: Sets the highest selectable number in the range.

Both fields accept dynamic and static values. Dynamic values are set using merge fields. For example, to use a Number element value, whose element name is Number1, to dynamically set your minimum or maximum value, enter %Number1%.

(Optional) For additional properties, see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions.
title: OmniScripts Range Element Configuration
